procstep.procdesc: The following steps were performed by ESRI: Extracted the four shapefiles (*eur_w_maj.shp) from AND Global Road Data and merged them into a single data set. Added the eastern boundary of the Caspian Sea with data originally from World Vector Shoreline. Removed the administrative boundary lines within all large divided water features. Added the CNTRYNAME attribute and coded it based on values from Europe Countries. Added the SQKM attribute and calculated its values. Added and coded the RANK attribute based on values from the SQKM attribute. Converted the data set to SDC. Created ArcGIS® layer file (.lyr), projection file (.prj), and spatial indices.

The following steps were performed by ESRI: Split Europe Major Water into major lakes and major rivers. Selected the lake features manually and output them into the Europe Major Lakes data set, switched the selection, and then output the remaining river features into the Europe Major Rivers data set. Converted the data sets to SDC and created their ArcGIS® layer files (.lyr), projection files (.prj), and spatial indices.

dataqual.logic: The shapefile is converted to SDC (Smart Data Compression) format using either ESRI SDC Data Development Kit Professional 2 (DDKP2) or tools in ArcGIS. The SDC data set is then loaded into ArcSDE® to verify and validate the geometry.
dataqual.complete: After processing, the data set is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.
